{"commentv2": 1, "number": 4, "id": 962355, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "43806", "body": "Bolvar becomes the new Lich king. In the cinematic Bolvar looks like he is made of rock and lava. \r\n\r\nhttp://www.youtube.com/watch?v=bJ0EJTeQ5gw\r\n\r\nHow did he get like this?", "date": "2010-02-01T16:08:16-06:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Several people have speculated that Bolvar is in fact Deathwing, which is probably very unlikely. But [i]could[/i] it be possible that Bolvar did, in fact, completely die at the wrathgate? And this  \"Lavaman\" character, could he be the human form of Deathwing, framing Bolvar to get the power of becoming the new Lich King?  I know I'm probably wrong, but it's just a thought.  Edit: I can actually prove myself wrong. Deathwing is currently in Deepholm, a completely different plane of existance. The second he sets foot on Azeroth, a huge explosion happens which is why all the zones will be partia", "creationdate": "2010-02-01T16:08:17-06:00", "id": 441101, "rating": 6, "commentid": 962355, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "ferdinand", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "That video has some major spoilers. Watch with caution! =P  On the topic of Bolvar's new \"rock and lava\" look, apparently he was exposed to Alexstrasza's Flame for too long when she and her Dragonflight cleansed the Wrathgate.", "creationdate": "2010-02-01T16:15:16-06:00", "id": 146470, "rating": 15, "commentid": 962355, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Mumpley", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 5, "id": 962369, "nreplies": 21, "sticky": 0, "user": "517387", "body": "[b]EXTREME LORE SPOILERS![/b]\n\nThe fate of Highlord Bolvar Fordragon is now clear and confirmed. He did indeed (as we already know) survive the battle at the Wrathgate. Being tortured by Arthas, Bolvar still refused to become his servant and champion.\n\nAfter the death of Arthas Menethil, Tirion was ready to take his place as the new Lich King in order to keep the Scourge at bay. However, just before he put on the Lich King's crown, a familiar voice shouted out to him.\n\nHighlord Bolvar Fordragon, engulfed in fires still burning from the purification of Alexstraza's red flame that was used to cleanse the Wrathgate, called out to Tirion. He convinced him to put the helmet of the Lich King on his head instead. Bolvar also told Tirion that none must know what truly went down in Icecrown Citadel that day, as if people were to realize that a Lich King was still alive, they could not avoid to live in fear and panic for the rest of their lives.\n\nRefusing at first, Tirion finally did what Bolvar asked him to. The eyes of the Lich King opened up once again, covering Bolvar's. The soul of one of the mightiest beings ever seen on Azeroth had corrupted a man who was pure at heart and true to all he believed in. Bolvar sealed himself as the Lich King in a block of ice and told Tirion to leave and never come back. This was the only way that Bolvar could aid the world now. He would forever keep the Scourge away from Azeroth.\n\nThe man who did something so great for the world he loves would be forgotten to cover up the existence of the Lich King. The man who boldly put the cursed crown on his head would do so without anyone knowing. And by the years he would always protect his beloved world in silence.\nThough no one would ever come to realize it, know that the end of the Scourge didn't come without a price. The world would've been destroyed if it wasn't for him.\n\nEven though his existence was meant to fade, always remember Highlord Bolvar Fordragon. A man who always wanted the best for his people and home. A hero till the end of his own days. \n\nAlways remember Highlord Bolvar Fordragon - The Lich King.", "date": "2010-02-01T16:23:07-06:00", "rating": 93, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Congradulations! You've just won Noobie of The Month!  Deathwing is sleeping Under Dun Algaz in the Wetlands, He's been sleeping their from after the Dragon Soul to his soontobe recent awakening.  Cataclysm has nothing to do with Arthas Cataclysm has nothing to do with Bovar Cataclysm has nothing to do with The Scourge Cataclysm has nothing to do with Cats (Although they do look cute)  Basically, Bovar will take the Throne as the new Lich king, only a few things remain that puzzle me...  What happens to Frostmourn? Does this mean that the Scourge has been destroyed? Is it possible that Bovar m", "creationdate": "2010-02-01T16:23:08-06:00", "id": 440670, "rating": 27, "commentid": 962369, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Cyonisper", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "[b]Spoilers/speculation.[/b]  The sword stole Arthas's soul, and the helm stole his humanity. We can't pretend that there isn't a chance that Bolvar, no matter how pure he was prior to the Lich King's torture, prior to the \"atrocities he committed on his soul\" that would forge him as the Scourge's next champion, could become just as dark as Arthas.  What made me go wild about the video was how Bolvar's voice quickly changed to the voice of Ner'zhul after he put on the helmet. Arthas and Ner'zhul both fused into a singular being that was contained inside of the crown, and there's no reason to b", "creationdate": "2010-02-01T16:23:08-06:00", "id": 440684, "rating": 12, "commentid": 962369, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "476166", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "What happens to Frostmourne?  After the fight with Arthas, Frostmourne is shattered unleashing a torrent of souls and possible giving Arthas his back for the last few seconds of his life. Arthas had his soul taken by the blade, Ner'zhul said it himself. Although they become one when Arthas donned the Crown of Dominaton  What happens to Bolvar Fordragon?  He becomes the new Lich King. Uther the Lightbringer and Terenas Menethil both knew that there must always be a Lich King, or the Scourge would simple be unleashed upon the Azeroth. With Frostmourne broken and Bolvar never taking hold of the b", "creationdate": "2010-02-01T16:23:08-06:00", "id": 440805, "rating": 7, "commentid": 962369, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "356379", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Just keep in mind that Arthas and Ner'zhul fused into one being, known as the Lich King. Once the Crown was off of Arthas' head, he was no longer the Lich King; though lore says Arthas no longer existed, the ending cinematic was proof that there was still an Arthas inside of that body, being controlled by something more powerful. Ner'zhul may have been destroyed as well, by Arthas after he donned the crown. But even as Arthas died, the Lich King still existed inside of that helm; the helm that Bolvar was desperate to wear.  The Lich King was a perfect fusion of two spirits, and we can now say ", "creationdate": "2010-02-01T16:23:08-06:00", "id": 443290, "rating": 6, "commentid": 962369, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "476166", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "[quote]The threat of the Scourge is still there and always will be, you could say they are simply under better management now. No doubt there is still alot of damage to repair across Azeroth.[/quote]  Curse you for putting this image in my head. I see him forcing the scourge to rebuild Azeroth. [b]\"Now, Under New Management!\"[/b]  Hordes of Geists and Ghouls dragging stone blocks and singing \"Heigh-ho, Heigh-ho, It's off to work we go!\" Lich-mages using magic to create permanent beautiful sculptures of ice, and hordes of Abominations singing \"Happy Worker\" from the movie \"Toy\"", "creationdate": "2010-02-12T17:35:49-06:00", "id": 148765, "rating": 24, "commentid": 962369, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "132039", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2010-02-11T07:55:44-06:00", 6, "517387"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 6, "id": 962593, "nreplies": 4, "sticky": 0, "user": "409680", "body": "Why is it always the Alliance that gets to have all the epic tales of self sacrifice for the greater good?\r\n\r\nThrall should have become the new King, would make sense in the new upcoming Cataclysm why he isn't Warchief", "date": "2010-02-01T22:46:09-06:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "No. Thrall has got much more important things to do.  With the fall or Arthas, the Lich King is gone. Do you want your greatest hero eternal oblivion?", "creationdate": "2010-02-02T00:49:27-06:00", "id": 146546, "rating": 5, "commentid": 962593, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "307852", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "The Alliance has many, many practitioners of the Light than the Horde, which is the ultimate enemy of the Shadow and undead. Blizz likes corrupting the uncorruptable.", "creationdate": "2010-02-02T10:38:30-06:00", "id": 146611, "rating": 6, "commentid": 962593, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "476166", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Luckily, Cataclysm will be all about Shamans. Thrall is a shaman, and  SPOILER  SPOILER  SPOILER  SPOILER  he controls the Maelstrom, which is why he can't be Warchief anymore. Thrall is actually one of the strongest shamans in game, according to lore.", "creationdate": "2010-09-25T13:23:44-05:00", "id": 183637, "rating": 2, "commentid": 962593, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "todiwan", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Well, I'd say Ner'zhul isn't dead, and although he is 'imprisoned' by Bolvar, he'd still hold the trophy for strongest shaman. I think just because he's considered a Lich doesn't mean his powers aren't still rooted in shamanism.", "creationdate": "2011-03-04T12:16:08-06:00", "id": 229958, "rating": 1, "commentid": 962593, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Ithuraen", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 7, "id": 963203, "nreplies": 4, "sticky": 0, "user": "menemew", "body": "Thralls head is too big to fit the helm, that's why. ^^", "date": "2010-02-02T15:14:43-06:00", "rating": 8, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "It fit Ner'zhul pretty well, I don't see why it wouldn't fit on Thrall too.", "creationdate": "2010-02-02T15:40:34-06:00", "id": 146662, "rating": 9, "commentid": 963203, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Pyromage", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "It never fit Ner'zhul, Ner'zhul fit it so to speak. He was literally torn apart and his soul stored for later use to be affixed to the armor like some cheap band patch sewn to a jacket. A very EVIL band patch.", "creationdate": "2010-02-03T21:40:47-06:00", "id": 146986, "rating": 13, "commentid": 963203, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Viggo", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "i think they should've forced garrosh to wear it. *thinks about hearing bombs going off all over the alliance capitals* on second thought maybe they shouldn't", "creationdate": "2010-03-09T17:19:31-06:00", "id": 153291, "rating": 6, "commentid": 963203, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "steinmetz342", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Oh lord, Ner'zhul would just pimp-slap him. Garrosh isn't as stubborn as Arthas or as sure of himself. He's ARROGANT but he's at heart still the bratty kid from Nagrand with the daddy issues.", "creationdate": "2011-11-01T00:09:07-05:00", "id": 274564, "rating": 2, "commentid": 963203, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "MiltiadesBooga", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 8, "id": 963298, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "260968", "body": "I know this might seem like a waste of time to write (and might not make ANY sense what-so-ever, or someone else might of said about some of the bellow previous to this post) however it's something I wanted to get off my chest. It's (to me, at least) interesting to note the sudden differences now between the \"new\" Lich King, as to when Arthas was the Lich King, in terms of appearance from the Video (for those who have seen it).\n \n - - - \n\nWhen Arthas Menethil placed the Helm (Helm of Domination) on for the very first time, it's interesting to note how the centre Gem was Blue (I believe Ner'zhul's soul is in the centre Gem? I can't recall) and how his eyes became inglufed in a Blue like aura of flames, which brought forth a new transformation from Arthas, to the Lich King. Considering how now, Bolvar Fordragon has now been given (or rather, requested, had) the Helm placed upon him, a similar transformation has undergone also. The Helm for starters (from what was shown) appears to be a more darker colour slightly, as well as the actual Gem housed within the centre of the Helm, turning from the Blue, to an Orange colour - along with the aura of flames (which were Blue, previous) coming from Bolvar's eyes now (which are also Orange).\n\n- - -\n\nIt also seems as if Bolvar is self-aware now, upon becoming the new Lich King as well (were as with Arthas, it seemed as if Ner'zhul was the one in control - as many simply assumed Arthas was no more - replaced by Ner'zhul - The Lich King, however the Frostmourne had a part to play on this act). Does this mean because Bolvar was exposed to Alexstrasza's flames for so long (as it's said her flames cleansed the Wrathgate, assuming it means it also cleansed the fallen there too, and because there is no Frostmourne, as it appears shattered on the floor, which was also the course of Arthas losing his mind, or soul rather) given the Lich King a new direction?", "date": "2010-02-02T17:09:23-06:00", "rating": 4, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "What would be epic is if when we finally get around to taking on Sargeras, Bolvar unleashes the scourge against the Burning Legion. Pit their own creation against them.", "creationdate": "2010-02-03T00:04:02-06:00", "id": 146752, "rating": 10, "commentid": 963298, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "JimesuEvil", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2010-02-02T17:19:05-06:00", 2, "260968"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 9, "id": 963449, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "314157", "body": "[quote]What happens to Frostmourne?[/quote]\r\n\r\nI'm guessing it will be destroyed somehow.\r\n\r\n[quote]Does this mean that the Scourge has been destroyed?[/quote]\r\n\r\nNo, Bolvar took the throne of the Lich King in order to control the scourge and keep them at bay, they will still exist, they will just not bring terror to the world anymore because they are now under the control of Bolvar.\r\n\r\n[quote]Is it possible that Bovar might be controlled by the spirit of Naz, Just like Arthas?[/quote]\r\n\r\nFrostmourne is like the ring in LOTR; Arthas was being controlled through frostmourne, as long as Bolvar doesn't go near frostmourne, I think he'll be alright, the answer to this question lies with the first question, if they find a way to destroy frostmourne, then the world will never have to fear the scourge again, I dont think its a coincidence that they didnt show what happened to frostmourne in the cinematic.\r\n\r\n[quote]What will Tirion do, now that Both the Crusade and Scourge have been delt with?[/quote]\r\n\r\nTirion for king of stormwind. I'd vote for him.\r\n\r\n[quote]He is told to not tell anyone, however both Sylvanis and Jaina know their must always be a Lich King.[/quote]\r\n\r\nHe will probably have to tell them I believe. It would be a secret between the three of them.\r\n\r\n[quote]Does this mean that the Light is more powerful then the Scourge? As it helped Bovar survive Arthas's endless torture.[/quote]\r\n\r\nProbably, and it helped.. defeat the lich king himself..", "date": "2010-02-02T20:10:52-06:00", "rating": 13, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 10, "id": 964674, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "farfalla", "body": "[quote]What happens to Frostmourne?[/quote]\nAt the beginning of the cinematic Frostmourne is shown lying next to Arthas. The blade is broken and shards are scattered around it. Presumably, it is this which allows players to take one and forge Shadowmourne out of it.\n\n[quote]Does this mean that the Scourge has been destroyed?[/quote]\nNo. The Crown of the Damned, the Lich King's helm, allows the wearer to control the Scourge. They will still exist and will be manipulated (for good or evil) by Bolvar.\n\n[quote]Is it possible that Bovar might be controlled by the spirit of Naz, Just like Arthas?[/quote]\nThis depends on whether Ner'zhul is alive (or, well, sentient.) There are contradictory sources on this. \n[ul]\n[li]In-game, we have the Tirion quest where you help destroy Arthas' heart, which Tirion can only allow himself to do after he's satisfied that Arthas is beyond redemption and no longer human.[/li]\n[li]We also have a Metzen quote - '\"Arthas and Ner'zhul have become a perfect fusion of one being - Arthas' personality and body with Ner'zhul's wisdom, experience, power and EVIL.\" Note however that I am unable to find a proper citation for this and the Wowwiki page I took it from does not have a citation either.[/li]\n[li]We have a blue post by Bornakk - 'Before Arthas donned the Lich King's armor, it was the spirit of the former Orc Shaman Ner'zhul whose soul was attached to the armor and then imprisoned (physically) inside the Frozen Throne. Now Arthas and Ner'zhul's spirit are one and together they are the Lich King.' However, the thread this was originally posted in is now AWOL and as such there is again no citation beyond Wowwiki.[/li]\n[/ul]\n\nOn the other hand, we have -\n[ul]\n[li]Golden's Arthas novel, which had Arthas slaughter the avatar of his humanity but then tell Ner'zhul that he didn't need him either and murder his avatar as well, after which Ner'zhul dissipated.[/li]\n[li]The fact that the cinematic for Arthas' deathscene has the Lich King glow fade from Arthas' eyes and he looks basically human again before he dies. Surely if Ner'zhul was still in there the glow would never fade?[/li]\n[/ul]\n\nWe know Arthas is dead. We don't know if Ner'zhul is dead - he didn't appear to die with Arthas, meaning the only thing which could have killed him is Arthas in his dreamstate in the novel. I don't know if he could do that. I also seem to remember the latest Twitter chat with the devs mentioning that they haven't told Ner'zhul's story yet in-game for a reason - because it's a good one and they want to do it right.\n\nIf he did? No, Ner'zhul can't corrupt Bolvar.\nIf he didn't, and Ner'zhul lives? I would say it's more than likely, and I'd say Blizzard are leaving the question over Ner'zhul's death unanswered for a reason.\n\n(Do note, though, that Arthas proved fairly easy to corrupt, in part due to personality traits (he was headstrong and slightly arrogant) which Bolvar does not share. Plus, Bolvar held out for a year against the Lich King already. I'd say it would be a lot harder to break Bolvar. On the other hand, looking at the cinematic, I think Bolvar was frightening (Tirion did the classic backing-away thing, and Bolvar's voice changed at the end) and I think he was frightening for a reason. \n\n[quote]What will Tirion do, now that Both the Crusade and Scourge have been delt with?[/quote]\nPresumably he'll go back to Stormwind with Varian, and act as a voice of reason. Or he'll be helping to deal with the Cataclysm events (I seem to remember that the Plaguelands is being changed up a lot, meaning maybe the Dawn will take it back?)\n\nOr, in three expansion's time, when the new Lich King unleases unholy hell on Azeroth again, he'll be banished again when people find out he (literally) crowned the King of the Damned. Who knows.\n\n[quote]He is told to not tell anyone, however both Sylvanis and Jaina know their must always be a Lich King.[/quote]\nWell, they know what Uther told them. Presumably they'll keep it quiet for the good of Azeroth. Or they'll listen when Tirion tells them that the Lich King is dead, nod, smile, and make a mental note to keep an eye on Icecrown...just in case.\n\n[quote]and lastly,\nDoes this mean that the Light is more powerful then the Scourge? As it helped Bovar survive Arthas's endless torture.[/quote]\nPaladins were immune to the plague due to the fact that they were imbued with the Light, so we know it's at least particularly resilient to shadow magic and disease. On the other hand, Bolvar is on fire because Alexstrasza breathed on him, and her flames bring life (if you look at the ground, they cause flowers to grow.) I think it's debatable whether the Light kept him alive, or whether Alexstrasza's flames did. As for the survival of the torture in a mental (remaining good) sense? Certainly.\n\nEdits:\n[quote]\nDont get me wrong, im not saying its true or untrue, but the first thing I thought about when I read that was: Onyxia had a human disguise in Stormwind too, Bolvar spent alot of time in Stormwind.. perhaps he planned this, perhaps that explains why he was not killed or purified and/or why Arthas could not break him.. Perhaps thats why Alexstrasza's flames affected him so.\n\nJust saying..[/quote]\n\nI'm not quite sure what you're saying here. Are you saying that Onyxia took a human form and hid in Katrana Prestor in Stormwind so maybe Deathwing did too and hid in Bolvar?\n\nIf so:\n[ul]\n[li]Deathwing did take a human form - Lord Daval Prestor. He attempted to cause strife during the Second War by buttering up Terenas so that he could marry Calia Menethil (Arthas' sister.) [/li]\n[li]You can also see Deathwing in human form during the fight with Yogg-Saron. He looks nothing like Bolvar.[/li]\n[li]If Deathwing had somehow been Bolvar, why would Bolvar aid in the original Onyxia attunement quest which involved Katrana Prestor being thrown out of Stormwind? You know, what with Onyxia being Deathwing's daughter and everything. Surely he'd just have dismissed your claim when you brought it to him, then had you killed quietly later.[/li]\n[/ul]", "date": "2010-02-03T13:13:39-06:00", "rating": 37, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Im sorry if I repeat something in your comment but there have been rumors that when Sylvanas went to The Frozen Throne she took the shards of Frostmourne she made them into arrows. This can be read about her going to the Throne in her short story on the armory and in the Shadowmourne quest line.", "creationdate": "2014-01-05T22:59:29-06:00", "id": 719597, "rating": 0, "commentid": 964674, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Aeitas", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2010-02-03T13:27:46-06:00", 1, "farfalla"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 11, "id": 965434, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "402784", "body": "[quote]What happens to Frostmourn?[/quote]\r\n\r\nWho cares? It's broke. They'll probably divide and scatter it in all corners of Azeroth and maybe Outland.\r\n\r\n[quote]Does this mean that the Scourge has been destroyed[/quote]\r\nAs far as I've interpreted, it's contained, now that Bolvar's the Lich King.\r\n\r\n[quote]Is it possible that Bovar might be controlled by the spirit of Naz, Just like Arthas?[/quote]\r\nProbably not. Ner'Zhul's original and main node of control on Arthas was Frostmourne, which he was manipulated extensively into acquiring. Bolvar has his spirit intact, and is set on the forzen throne with one simple purpose: Keep the Scourge at bay. Ner'Zhul may be able to whisper, but Bolvar can resist/ignore him.\r\n\r\n[quote]What will Tirion do, now that Both the Crusade and Scourge have been delt with?[/quote]\r\nI'd imagine continue to lead the Argent Crusade and act as a second defense should the Scourge break out again.\r\n\r\n[quote]He is told to not tell anyone, however both Sylvanis and Jaina know their must always be a Lich King.[/quote]\r\n\r\nYes, but their gripe was with Arthas.\r\n\r\n[quote]Does this mean that the Light is more powerful then the Scourge? As it helped Bovar survive Arthas's endless torture. [/quote]\r\nI would like to imagine that Bolvar's will was just too strong to be corrupted to the extent of what Arthas did to him.", "date": "2010-02-04T06:41:53-06:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 12, "id": 965753, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "476166", "body": "[quote]Unfortunately according to a friend who read the \"Rise of the Lich King\" book, it is revealed that Ner'zhul was somehow destroyed by Arthas in a conflict in his mind (crazy eh?). However Ner'zhul can still exist, but I believe at the very least I can safely say that most of his will/memories have been destroyed.[/quote]\r\nAccording to Metzen, both Ner'zhul and Arthas were fused into one singular being. According to the book, Arthas dominates the Lich King in this fusion; while it does seem to imply that Ner'zhul was killed, lore implies more strongly that the Lich King is both and neither at once. It's an entity by itself. Quests in the Icecrown (like when the Lich King claims that he was once a Shaman) further implies that both share the body.\r\n\r\nThe fusion was created as soon as the Arthas put on that crown, meaning that everything that was the old Lich King (memories, powers, etc) was contained inside of that crown too. Once the two fused, that means everything that was Arthas was contained inside of that helm too, mixing with Ner'zhul.\r\n\r\nAs soon as the helm gets thrown off in the video, Arthas no longer has vision; all he sees is darkness, and his once-glowing eyes become normal. He no longer has a distorted voice, and seems to recognize his father's presence before his death. We can attribute that to \"normal\" Arthas -- this was due to his separation from both the crown's control, and having his soul released by the Frostmourne.\r\n\r\nWhen Bolvar puts on the helmet, he gains glowing eyes and the Lich King's voice. He fuses with the Lich King entity of Ner'zhul and Arthas, just as Arthas did. From watching the video, he just *seems* very sinister. Bolvar seems inexplicably drawn to that helmet, and appears to be single-minded and focused on it. And with the Lich King discussing how he tortured Bolvar's soul, how he was to be his next great Champion, and how Yogg-Saron showed that he influenced this torture, it all seems to amount to the scenario being far more than what we may think, which I think just makes it more epic.\r\n\r\nI'm trying to say, maybe Bolvar *didn't* ultimately resist the Lich King's torture. Maybe it was planned; maybe, all along, the entity that was the Lich King knew that it needed a new host, one that would be left alone by Azeroth while the Scourge recoups. One that needed the world to think the Lich King was dead, and that the Scourge was no longer a danger. And Bolvar seems like the perfect candidate.", "date": "2010-02-04T11:57:18-06:00", "rating": 12, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 13, "id": 965791, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "shadowspa", "body": "[quote]What happens to Frostmourn?[/quote]\n\n[b][i]Spoilers from the Lich King fight[/i][/b]\n                                |      \n                                |\n                                |\n\nWhen you get him to low health,he will oneshot the raid(and you can't release spirit,ofcourse.)\n\nHe will then tell Tirion,who has been encased in a block of ice since the begining of the encounter that he foresaw the fight,and that in [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?zone=4722]training[/url] you,he had strengtened you for his use,that you will serve him as his greatest champions.\n\nHe begins to raise you as scourge,but before he finishes the cast,Tirion,pleading the light for the strenght to break the prison,breaks free and leaps at the Lich King,striking and shattering Frostmourne with Ashbringer.All spirits are released,including King Terenas.\n\nAs the spirits lift Arthas into the air and strangulate him,Terenas mass ressurects the raid,and the last few percents of the fight are basicly,like Archimonde,a certain victory,as he you nuke the last remaining hp from the suspended Arthas.", "date": "2010-02-04T12:56:44-06:00", "rating": 8, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "if you try to release (if it doesnt bug) a message comes up stating you are OWNED by the lich king. a nice touch", "creationdate": "2013-02-05T05:03:15-06:00", "id": 629816, "rating": 0, "commentid": 965791, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 256, "username": "Tenjen", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2010-02-04T15:39:32-06:00", 3, "shadowspa"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 14, "id": 966195, "nreplies": 5, "sticky": 0, "user": "222376", "body": "So here's something that's been boggling my mind since I've seen the cinematic.\r\nBolvar has taken the role of the Lich King, with the Helm of Domination sealing his fate.   This would, of course, give him the greatest control of death in the Warcraft universe.   And, alongside this, he would obviously gain powerful frost powers, just due to the nature of the climate and all that.\r\n\r\nBut he HAS been infused with the flame of the Red Dragonflight, which is the flame that gives life.\r\n\r\nBasically, Bolvar is now a walking oxymoron.\r\n\r\nLife + Death\r\nFire + Ice", "date": "2010-02-04T21:56:18-06:00", "rating": 49, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "[quote trogodor] Bolvar is now a walking oxymoron.[/quote]  What are you talking about? He's sitting, bro.", "creationdate": "2010-02-04T23:43:39-06:00", "id": 147199, "rating": 47, "commentid": 966195, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "402784", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Champion of good is incinerated, twisted beyond recognition and eventually brings balance to the ForcWAIT A SECOND!", "creationdate": "2010-02-10T16:56:20-06:00", "id": 148400, "rating": 29, "commentid": 966195, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "taeralis", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "You have recieved [b][Crown of Domination][/b]. The (New) Lich King has learned a new spell: Frostfire Strike.", "creationdate": "2010-03-06T08:36:13-06:00", "id": 444082, "rating": 7, "commentid": 966195, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "PinkWolf", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "vot