{"commentv2": 1, "number": 18, "id": 973112, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "211544", "body": "I cannot possibly fathom the amount of Willpower required to actually [b]RESIST THE LICH KING :|[/b]\r\n\r\nI mean;\r\n\r\nHe got burned - \r\nBurned again - \r\nHis soul has been defiled\r\nAnd on and on and I can go on what other horrifying ....things, The Lich King did to him.\r\n\r\nHell, that pansy ass green dragon in ICC didn't had  that much willpower either, or Saurfang, or even Arthas! Although there is a possibility Bolvar will become corrupt somehow from the helm of Domination/Dominion/Dominance.\r\n\r\nThe future will tell, although I'm sure we haven't heard the last from Ner'zhul.", "date": "2010-02-11T09:45:42-06:00", "rating": 7, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Saurfang Jr. and Arthas both had their souls taken by Frostmourne, so they had little to no choice  but to become servants of Lich King. Bolvar has the heart of true paladin, so his mental resistance is almost impassable.BTW, why didn't Lich King try to take Bolvar's soul by Frostmourne? I mean, it's easy, just poke him with sharp side, isn't it?", "creationdate": "2010-07-03T14:50:29-05:00", "id": 171293, "rating": 3, "commentid": 973112, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "HedinTC", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "I believe he wanted him to be his champion. All \"high ranking\" scourge are actually self-aware, not mindless undead.", "creationdate": "2010-09-25T13:54:22-05:00", "id": 183643, "rating": 1, "commentid": 973112, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "todiwan", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
