{"commentv2": 1, "number": 31, "id": 1006865, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "seanlong", "body": "uh we all know why arthas died because when the frostmourne was shattered it freed all the souls inculing arthas's but arthas only had a few mins to live to say his last words then he died but the only resion he died was because no human body could live without a heart so that's how the lich king a.k.a arthas died so if arthas still had his heart now when the frostmourne shattered he could of hold the scourge back because arthas was good again, so that's the only resion arthas died the night the frostmourne shattered because no human body could survire without a heart\r\n\r\nhope that helps", "date": "2010-03-28T01:42:01-05:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Translation:  We know how the Lich King was defeated and that Arthas' soul returned to his body after Frostmourne was shattered But the reason as to why Arthas died was because not long after he became the Lich King, he tore out his own heart as he saw it as a weakness. Without his heart, or his status as an Undead/Immortal, instead being a human once again, he only had moments to live before death via Lack-of-a-heart.  Added tid-bits of my own:  While his lack of a heart would obviously mean that he would have died, We also kick his ass in a raid, Tirion shatters the blade which causes the fu", "creationdate": "2010-03-28T01:42:02-05:00", "id": 447187, "rating": 7, "commentid": 1006865, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "whitedragon254", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "actually his body is not human, its still unfused with the unspeakable effects of being the lich kings mortal coil and having those energies. He dies because his sword was smashed and we beat the ever living stuffing out of him.", "creationdate": "2013-02