{"commentv2": 1, "number": 38, "id": 1144774, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "288482", "body": "[quote]What will Tirion do now that the Scarlet Onslaught and the Scourge have been dealt with?[/quote]\r\n\r\nWell him and his own little crusading buddies decide to take back Hearthglen in Western Plaguelands. Hearthglen becomes a Questing Hub for the mid 40s range. He does not become an advisor to Varian Wrynn. That is just ridiculous. That shows favoritism. The entire time in Northrend he is telling Alliance and Horde players that united they will defeat the Lich King but seperated they will fall. Now that the Lich King is dead, he is not going to say \"Well thanks for the help, Horde, you were a big help in that fight but I'm going to go roll Alliance. Later\"\r\n\r\nIt is unknown at the moment if he starts another faction, stays with the Argent Crusade, or returns to the Argent Dawn.", "date": "2010-10-16T21:40:01-05:00", "rating": 4, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 39, "id": 1156043, "nreplies": 4, "sticky": 0, "user": "111622", "body": "Doesn't make sense, at the Wrathgate, Alexstraza approached and mourned the death of Bolvar. Then she handed him over to Arthas?\r\n\r\nLet me get this straight, Bolvar wanted the Lich King position instead of Tirion because he was already presumed dead and other reasons. But he also wanted it instead of Arthas, so that he could [i]prevent[/i] the Scourge from destroying Azeroth? Couldn't we just simply put an end to the Scourge? The Lich King's original duty was to destroy Azeroth, but now that Bolvar has taken that seat upon the Frozen Throne, what's to come of that huge Scourge Army that Arthas raised? They're still there, will he just let us take them all out?\r\n\r\nAnd what about Frostmourne, it's what corrupted Arthas in the first place, it could do that to Bolvar too, right?", "date": "2010-10-29T11:21:18-05:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Frostmourne is Broken, shattered and gone.  Alexstraza could not save Surfang and Bovar, both were captured by ghouls and raised as death knights by Arthas himself.  Surfang the younger took this as a revival, being a warrior he had no resistance to the light and was overcome by shadow.  Bovar fought on, he wouldn not let Arthas control him... so Arthas tourtured him... hoping to break Bovar and turn him into a powerful weapon.  Now that Bovar is the Lich king, Engulfed by the Flames of Alexstraza's children, he sit atop his thron attempting to control the scourge which has been a threat to ou", "creationdate": "2010-10-29T11:21:19-05:00", "id": 462451, "rating": 3, "commentid": 1156043, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Cyonisper", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "1) In chronological order - the Reds burned Bolvar/Saurfang, Arthas dragged them with him (back into Icecrown), Alexstrazsa saw this and landed. She didn't \"hand him over,\" they were already gone.  2) That \"huge Scourge army\" is just that, still HUGE. And yes, that is exactly what's happening - the Argent Crusade is rooting out the rest of the Scourge. However, you have to keep in mind the command structure of the Scourge, a bit chaotic though it is - necromancers, etc, the whole Cult of the Damned is still out there (albeit without its strongest leaders, Kel'thuzad, Lady Deathwhisper, and of ", "creationdate": "2010-10-29T11:21:19-05:00", "id": 483754, "rating": 1, "commentid": 1156043, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Strudels", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Too bad Sylvanas doesn't agree. She thinks Bolvar will get power to his head all the same as Arthas did. http://www.wowpedia.org/The_Lich_King#One_King_Falls.2C_Another_Rises", "creationdate": "2012-11-30T09:22:23-06:00", "id": 605366, "rating": 1, "commentid": 1156043, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "DagothUr", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Sylvanas is a TERRIBLE judge of character, she's scheming and people like she is now, can only think of other people as being as toxic and manipulative as her. Her opinion has ZERO weight. She didnt even know bolvar and has been depressive and treacherous for years and getting worse. Not that she isnt awesome or may not be right, but till we see what Bolvar becomes on the flip side, her opinion is irrelevant.", "creationdate": "2013-02-05T04:56:30-06:00", "id": 629814, "rating": 1, "commentid": 1156043, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 256, "username": "Tenjen", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
