{"commentv2": 1, "number": 42, "id": 1725709, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "Drakanthor264", "body": "Well I am just guessing but wasn't Ner'zhul's soul and life in Frostmourne? Because Arthas wielded the sword being corrupted by him turning him into the Lich King, so maybe Bolvar won't be corrupted by Ner'Zhul being that the sword was destroyed but also we saw some sort of spirit fly from the broken blade so maybe now he will try to find a weapon he can merge with and wait until another poor soul wields him so he may control.", "date": "2012-09-30T07:22:20-05:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Not entirely accurate. There were three spirits fighting for control inside of Frostmourne: the evil death knight Arthas Menethil, Ner'zhul, and a personification of Arthas' remaining humanity, Matthias Lehner (This was all during a dream). Arthas killed Matthias, and Ner'zhul was delighted by this, declaring that he and Arthas could now merge spirits into one being. However, Arthas rejected the offer, and impaled and stunned Ner'zhul, stating that since he had the power of the Lich king no one can tell him what to do ever again. http://www.wowpedia.org/The_Lich_King#The_Lich_King_Triumphant", "creationdate": "2012-11-30T09:14:15-06:00", "id": 605364, "rating": 1, "commentid": 1725709, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "DagothUr", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Nerzhul is not inside the sword, he's in the helm. Or atleast was till he merged with Arthas and had his aspect within the new LK destroyed by what proved to be a more dominant Arthas aspect.", "creationdate": "2013-02-05T04:51:43-06:00", "id": 629813, "rating": 1, "commentid": 1725709, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 256, "username": "Tenjen", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, 