{"commentv2": 1, "number": 4, "id": 539819, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Maxtro", "body": "Highlord Bolvar Fordragon used to be Regent Lord of Stormwind ruling in King Varian Wrynn's absence. He was very involved in the quest chain to get attuned for Onyxia. \r\n\r\nWhen King Wrynn returned, Fordragon was sent to Northrend to attack the Lich King. He is currently at Fordragon Hold in the Dragonblight.", "date": "2008-12-31T13:33:13-06:00", "rating": 16, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 5, "id": 542964, "nreplies": 7, "sticky": 0, "user": "Grinton", "body": "Hey I'm trying to put together an outfit to look just like Bolvar Fordragon, can anyone help me, expecially in regards to the sword and shield.\n\nThanks\n\nEdit:  Corrected name", "date": "2009-01-02T12:35:35-06:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "All sets are [b]Alliance only[/b].  Paladins: [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?itemset=402]Epic[/url]  [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?itemset=544]Rare[/url]  or  Warriors: [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?itemset=384]Epic[/url]  [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?itemset=282]Rare[/url]  Combined with [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?item=12584]This sword[/url] and [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?item=18825]This shield[/url].  Happy gathering, and rest assured, when you wear this, heads will turn, its just [i]that[/i] badass.  I play horde, but i think those are one/two of the most awesome sets in WoW.  *edit* Stella", "creationdate": "2009-01-02T12:35:36-06:00", "id": 394447, "rating": 7, "commentid": 542964, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 256, "username": "2OfDiamonds", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Bolvar Fordragon and Tirion Fordring are two very different people.", "creationdate": "2009-01-03T12:57:01-06:00", "id": 69878, "rating": 9, "commentid": 542964, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "192801", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Bolver's NEW outfit in Wrath is the 60 warrior or paladin set.", "creationdate": "2009-01-10T01:18:30-06:00", "id": 71632, "rating": 4, "commentid": 542964, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "259138", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "@ 2OfDiamonds:  Do you know which belt he's wearing? Pretty please?", "creationdate": "2009-05-28T01:11:25-05:00", "id": 100525, "rating": 1, "commentid": 542964, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "370722", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "He still is using the Epic Shoulders, Gloves and Chest for sure.", "creationdate": "2010-01-04T05:08:25-06:00", "id": 141182, "rating": 2, "commentid": 542964, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "268034", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2009-01-04T13:38:15-06:00", 1, "Grinton"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 6, "id": 545303, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "193821", "body": "Something tells me he is not completely lost yet... There is a dialogue you see when Alexstrasza is talking to Korialstrasz but due to a a bug where some players can speak Draconic, some players are able to read and translate the line of text that Alexstrasza says\r\n\r\nThe line of text reads: \r\nAlexstrasza: [Draconic] They must not discover the fate of the young paladin. Not yet. \r\n\r\nThis may mean that Bolvar is alive somehow, or that he was not \"purified\" by the flames of the red dragons. Perhaps, he was taken to safe place by Red Dragonflight or captured by the Scourge.", "date": "2009-01-03T19:53:34-06:00", "rating": 20, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "[quote]due to a a bug where some players can speak Draconic, some players are able to read and translate the line of text that Alexstrasza says[/quote]  When patch 3.0.2 was released, the gates of Ahn'Qiraj were briefly closed due to a bug that reset the gates on each server, and gave all characters of the same Race and Class as the original opener the ability to speak Draconic.  Taken from Wowwiki.", "creationdate": "2009-04-05T04:12:39-05:00", "id": 89457, "rating": 9, "commentid": 545303, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "240917", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 7, "id": 565615, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "executorvgk", "body": "[quote]The line of text reads:\r\nAlexstrasza: [Draconic] They must not discover the fate of the young paladin. Not yet.\r\n\r\nThis may mean that Bolvar is alive somehow, or that he was not \"purified\" by the flames of the red dragons. Perhaps, he was taken to safe place by Red Dragonflight or captured by the Scourge.[/quote]\r\ninteresting theory however some of it does not make sense for me if we must not discover his fate  why shouldn't we know he's alive or wouldn't some one have seen him or something also this gas cloud thing made by putress injured the Lich King while only being in it temporarily Bolvar and his men were in it much longer .\r\nWhich leads me to conclude that Bolvar is amongst the undead now either as one of them or as a prisoner however history of the scourge would show contrary of him being a prisoner\r\n please leave some of your opinion i want to hear what you got to say on this", "date": "2009-01-16T18:54:35-06:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 8, "id": 587160, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "202286", "body": "[quote]interesting theory however some of it does not make sense for me if we must not discover his fate why shouldn't we know he's alive or wouldn't some one have seen him or something also this gas cloud thing made by putress injured the Lich King while only being in it temporarily Bolvar and his men were in it much longer .\r\nWhich leads me to conclude that Bolvar is amongst the undead now either as one of them or as a prisoner however history of the scourge would show contrary of him being a prisoner\r\nplease leave some of your opinion i want to hear what you got to say on this[/quote]\r\n\r\nYes, this could be true that he has joined either the Scourge or Forsaken, however, one thing we haven't even dared to look at is whether or not he was found and taken by the Red Dragonflight, where he might attempt to be cleansed. If you think about it, Putress basically walked off, Lich King fell back, and almost all of the living either died in the gas or ran away. Bolvar was exposed to the gas for a very short amount of time before the Reds came to purify the area, so it is possible he is Undead, and is now in the Red Chamber(Chamber of the Aspects) where he could possibly be cleansed...", "date": "2009-01-29T19:40:39-06:00", "rating": -1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 9, "id": 608658, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "drac", "body": "Although he's marked as a Boss, he wont aggro if you go near him or \"inside\" of him :D\nHe will attack only if a nearby NPC attacks you.\nAnd he hits for 5k on 13k armor. ( just as a refference )\nThe nearby NPC use a [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?spell=49482]Stormhammer[/url] ability, which is a Physical attack and can be mitigated by armor, but its a range attack.\n[quote][Fordragon Gryphon Rider] [Stormhammer] hit [You] 1076 Physical. [/quote]", "date": "2009-02-14T05:41:25-06:00", "rating": 3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "He's actually soloable as a Prot Pally or Feral Druid without much trouble. Assuming you get to 80 and get half-decent gear without doing the Wrath Gate questline somehow. (I did it on the PTR)", "creationdate": "2009-07-12T02:34:00-05:00", "id": 415193, "rating": 1, "commentid": 608658, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "133226", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2009-02-14T05:43:03-06:00", 1, "drac"]}
