{"commentv2": 1, "number": 11, "id": 631875, "nreplies": 3, "sticky": 0, "user": "Daxmort", "body": "[b]SPOILERS.[/b]\n...\n...\n...\n...\n...\n...\nAccording to new soundclips from the 3.1 PTR, during the Yogg-Saron fight, you are shown scenes from the past (or just different times);\n\n- Creation of the Dragonsoul (Ysera, Neltharion/Deathwing and Malygos).\n\n- Some chatter between King Llane and Garona during the siege on Stormwind.\n\n- And lastly, Arthas/The Lich King torturing someone; the sound files only say 'Arthas_Prisoner'. However, the voice sounds exceedingly similar to Bolvar.\n\n\"Your resistance..is..admirable..\"\n\n\"*Choking, pained sounds.* MONSTER! I am...not afraid of you..! *Random screams.*\"\n\n\"I will break you..as I broke him.\" (Him: Saurfang?)\n\nSimply speculation of course, but hopefully, we'll see Bolvar as a Death Knight at some point in the future.\n\nEdit: [url=http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=B6Pht3iRq8Y]Link for those interested.[/url]", "date": "2009-03-05T06:02:45-06:00", "rating": 8, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "I will brake you {Darion Morgraine} as I broke Him {Alexander Morgraine}", "creationdate": "2009-03-24T13:40:23-05:00", "id": 395898, "rating": 1, "commentid": 631875, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "335096", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "He probably survived the fire from the dragons because he threw on his Fire resist gear from MC", "creationdate": "2009-06-03T21:06:27-05:00", "id": 101801, "rating": 25, "commentid": 631875, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "330185", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Daxmort called it.", "creationdate": "2010-06-24T20:43:57-05:00", "id": 169818, "rating": 1, "commentid": 631875, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Alias365", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2009-03-05T06:05:08-06:00", 2, "Daxmort"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 12, "id": 635902, "nreplies": 4, "sticky": 0, "user": "159686", "body": "---------------------------------SPOILER ALERT, if you do not wish to know the conclusion of the quest-chain, then DO NOT read this comment!----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nWhen you have completed the long - and truly epic - quest chain, Saurfang the Younger and Highlord Bolvar confronts the Lich King. Saurfang gets slain by Frostmourne (and the Lich King does something that looks like extracting a soul or something), and Grand Apothecary Putress attacks the Lich King with his own plague, weakening the Lich King - and killing the remains of the Horde and Alliance forces in the process. Then Alexstrasza and her Red Dragonflight comes and scorches the ground, removing Putress's plague. When you come back from the cutscene, all soldiers at the Alliance, and Horde base is fleeing in terror, and Alexstrasza and Korialstrasz are talking in the aftermath of the battle. Their conversation is:\n    \nKorialstrasz says: My Queen, do they know? \n    Alexstrasza the Life-Binder says: No, my beloved. \n    Alexstrasza the Life-Binder says: [Draconic] Ashj zila gul kirasath lok ante il lok buras danashj Gul gul \n    Korialstrasz nods. \n    Korialstrasz says: They will not. \n    Alexstrasza whispers: Come to me, <name>. \n\nIf you had completed the quest-chain involving Ahn'Qiraj, on the test servers, you were able to understand what Alexstrasza said, and it is: They must not discover the fate of the young paladin. Not yet. \nThis implies that Bolvar maybe survived one way or another. My personal theory is that both Bolvar and Saurfang will be a boss encounter in the raid version of Icecrown Citadel that is to be released in a future patch. One of the reasons why I believe this, is because I hope it is like that. Second is because it would be a great demoraliser to both the Horde and Alliance to see their former Heroes turned into Death Knights of the Scourge.", "date": "2009-03-08T17:32:32-05:00", "rating": 10, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Before I mention anything, if you disagree go ahead and downrate.  I like Bolvar as a person. He acts like your average everyday warrior, here to defend Stormwind and its people, and therein lies the problem. Although I think Bolvars a good military leader, under him as regent lord Stormwind kingdom wasnt doing so hot; we had no real king, we had corrupt politicians, we had Onyxia sneaking in the backround, and so on. The army wasnt even doing its job, it was practically chillin off in some unknown land while we deal with the problems. With all due respect to sir Fordragon, hes a good highlord", "creationdate": "2009-03-08T17:32:33-05:00", "id": 405170, "rating": 10, "commentid": 635902, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "346157", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Because Icecrown is full of http://www.wowhead.com/?npc=32255, we can obviously assume that it isn't beyond the Lich King to ressurect fallen heroes and bring them into battle under his control. I'm thinking of two heroes in particular who are due to come back as bosses.  http://www.wowhead.com/?npc=33442 is apparently the npc which Arthas tortures in one of Yogg-Saron's visions. According to rumor he has similar armor to Bolvar. Additionally, the npc's name is \"Immolated Champion\", and Bolvar's body was supposedly cleansed of corruption by Alexstrasza's [b]fire[/b] after the Wrathgate events.", "creationdate": "2009-03-08T17:32:33-05:00", "id": 409281, "rating": 4, "commentid": 635902, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Megalomania", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "He [b]was[/b] under Onyxia's control with a medallion she used.", "creationdate": "2009-05-26T02:07:54-05:00", "id": 100145, "rating": 5, "commentid": 635902, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "VraulJawrip", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "I would say u guessed really good, saurfang is a raid encount and bolvar is taken by the lich king, maybe even used in the battle against him, this is said the week before the lich king gets released so dont know the fight especially good, but u still guessed VERY good, also could u learn me to speak Draconic, your translation was so IMBA :)", "creationdate": "2010-01-27T16:36:37-06:00", "id": 145624, "rating": 2, "commentid": 635902, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "357354", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2009-03-08T17:34:30-05:00", 1, "159686"]}
