{"commentv2": 1, "number": 4, "id": 2279489, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "step2me", "body": "I bet he is going to be happy being able to talk to someone that isn't a demented ner'zhul. Referring to Nobbel87's speculation about trapping someone back into the shards of frostmourne, maybe it is nerzhul, and we free bolvar? Then he becomes a powerful deathknight like the rest of us, and comes to be one of the champions?", "date": "2015-11-23T18:49:46-06:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Ner'zhul is a seperate npc in the files but is also retains the title of Lich King. its very likely that he is the last spirit that ust be \"tamed\" within the shattered remains of Frostmourne, as it would be rather fitting that the original Lich King was one of the few souls not freed from the accursed blade....", "creationdate": "2015-11-23T19:27:37-06:00", "id": 913400, "rating": 1, "commentid": 2279489, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "conmanW", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Ner'zhul's presence is just as an echo, not the real deal. Arthas got rid of Ner'zhul in his book.", "creationdate": "2016-03-22T10:28:05-05:00", "id": 935197, "rating": 0, "commentid": 2279489, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 256, "username": "Reignac", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2015-11-23T18:50:06-06:00", 1, "step2me"]}
